# type (If applied, this commit will...) <subject> (Max 72 char)
# |<----   Preferably using up to 50 chars   --->|<------------------->|
# Example:
# feat: add new features
# Example with scope:
# feat(scope): add new features

# (Optional) Explain why this change is being made
# |<----   Try To Limit Each Line to a Maximum Of 72 Characters   ---->|

# (Optional) Provide links or keys to any relevant tickets, articles or other resources
# Example: Github issue #23

# build     Fix CI Build
# chore     Mundane tasks
# ci        Changes reguarding CI
# docs      Write docs / Update docs
# feat      Introduce new features
# fix       Fix a bug
# perf      Improve performance
# refactor  Any refactor
# revert    Revert a previous change
# style     Improve structure / format of the code
# test      Add tests

# --------------------
# Remember to:
#   * Add a colon after the type of commit
#   * Not capitalize the subject line
#   * Use the imperative mood in the subject line
#   * Do not end the subject line with a period
#   * Separate subject from body with a blank line
#   * Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
#   * Can use multiple lines with "-" or "*" for bullet points in body
# --------------------
